  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>ey Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Develop and lead business development strategies for international sourcing and import operations</li><li>Identify, evaluate, and onboard overseas manufacturers and exporters to support business growth</li><li>Build and manage long-term commercial relationships with suppliers, distributors, and key accounts</li><li>Lead pricing, contract negotiations, and commercial agreements</li><li>Conduct market analysis and demand forecasting to guide sourcing and expansion decisions</li><li>Coordinate with internal teams on logistics planning, import documentation, customs clearance, and regulatory compliance</li><li>Ensure compliance with Singapore import regulations and food trade requirements</li><li>Prepare business plans, revenue forecasts, and management reports</li><li>Represent the company in strategic meetings, negotiations, and trade discussions</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Master’s Degree in Business Administration or any related field.</li><li>Minimum <strong>1 – 10 years of relevant experience</strong> in Business Development, International Trade, or Import & Export</li><li>Proven experience managing <strong>cross-border trade operations</strong> and supplier relationships</li><li>Strong knowledge of <strong>FMCG or grocery product supply chains</strong>, logistics, and trade documentation</li><li>Demonstrated ability to negotiate complex commercial agreements independently</li><li><strong>Bilingual communication skills</strong> (English and at least one additional business language) to support coordination with overseas suppliers and partners</li><li>Strong leadership, stakeholder management, and execution capabilities</li><li>Willing to travel overseas if required</li></ul>",
